<DOC><DOCNO> AP880405-0017 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-05-88 0205EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-WISCONSINAt-A-Glance     04-05 0198</FIRST><SECOND>PM-WISCONSIN At-A-Glance,160</SECOND><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here, at a glance, are the methods for pickingdelegates from Wisconsin to attend the 1988 Democratic andRepublican national conventions this summer.</TEXT><HEAD>DEMOCRATS</HEAD><TEXT>   Method: Primary   Date: Tuesday, April 5   Pledged delegates: 81 Super delegates: 7 TOTAL: 88   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, April 5   Selection of delegates:Sunday, May 22 and Saturday, June 11      All of Wisconsin's 81 pledged delegates to the DemocraticNational Convention will be allocated among presidential candidatesin proportion to the results of the primary on April 5.</TEXT><HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD><TEXT>   Method: Primary   Date: Tuesday, April 5   Delegates: 47   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, April 5   Selection of delegates: Dates not yet determined.      All of Wisconsin's delegates to the Republican NationalConvention will be allocated among presidential candidates based onthe results of the primary.   The presidential candidate receiving a plurality of votes in acongressional district will get all three of the nationalconvention delegates from that district.   The remaining 20 delegates at large will go to the presidentialcandidate receiving a plurality of the statewide vote.   After the primary, the state committee will submit a list ofnational convention delegates for approval by the winningpresidential candidates.</TEXT></DOC>